 is great but u must be in group or shoot someone elses pull because your bow will ONLY do double damage if mob is not rooted and if mob is not targeted on u.  My highest critical with some  shammy buffs is 198 currently w/ a Raincaller, summoned 3/50 arrows from tolan bracer, 124dex.  I don't know when it starts but my lvl 60 ranger friend hits quad damage w/ his bow.  In KC, he KSed the lcy group from the rcy with his trueshot discipline.  Hope this helps someone.<br><br>Finkk McFinkklestein<br>52nd Ranger<br>Druzzil Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#006400><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/usaaldonraginstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saaldon Raginstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ADFF2f>(3/5/02 5:05:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.users.uswest.net/~ckelley5/saal02.BMP WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Archery</span><hr size=1> If you want big damage get a great bow.. I have a Velium 30/40 and a Bow of Underfoot 33/60 and stats. Get a great quiver and 33/60 is quite insane. Next make 6 damage arrows. You will average 170-200+ easy with dbl damage no disc needed. With disc. you will average about the same but seem to get the real big crits and way more hits with very few misses if any some rounds. A few nights ago w/o disc or a dbl damage I hit a few times in 650+ range.. That is 1300 plus crit.. Still waiting but I know it can be done now. <br><br> <p>Saaldon Raginstorm... <BR>Loyal Captain of the Brew </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#006400><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uytrill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ytrill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#ADFF2f>(3/5/02 11:36:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.kc.rr.com/witchdoctor/ytrill7.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Archery</span><hr size=1> Weaponshield disc is at level 60.<br><br>You get double damage bow shots when the MOB is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not moving</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and is not rooted.<br><br>To put points into archery mastery (or any other Class AA skill), you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> must</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be level 59 and have invested at least 6 points in General and 12 points in Archetype AA skills. General skill points can be earned starting at level 51, and can be spent right away, since all the General AA skills can be raised with one AA point. Archetype skills can be earned starting at level 55, and increase in price on a sliding scale of 2/4/6 points for each additional level. Therefore, to even think about putting points into Archery Mastery, you have to AA &quot;ding&quot; at least 30 times (6*1)+(12*2)=30.<br><br>Needless to say, it is a very large investment of time. <p><font size=2, face=legends, arial><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27521><b>Ytrill Stonebow (Magelo Profile)</b></a><br>3rd Season Pathfinder<br>Destiny Awaits - E'ci</font></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm3.showNextMessage?topicID=155.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table